def calculate_min_height(n: int, k: int) -> int:
    """
    Calculate the minimum possible height of a plot consisting of 2n+1 vertices
    and having an area equal to k.

    Parameters:
    n (int): The number of vertices in the plot.
    k (int): The required area of the plot.

    Returns:
    int: The minimum possible height of the plot.
    """
    return (k - 1 + n) / n
